From 995079377081f4ef92618453a70307ac8e698422 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tamizh Chelvam Raja <tamizhr@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sun, 31 Aug 2025 00:47:18 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:DP:wifi:ath12k: Fix filling skb_cb flags for non fast
 xmit packet

In case of packet goes through non fast Tx path ath12k_wifi7_dp_tx()
it expects ATH12K_SKB_CIPHER_SET flag to be filled in skb_cb->flags.
As it uses the flag check for software encrypted(DVLAN) packet in
native wifi mode. By not setting this flag would cause filling
htt meta data for the packet and adding msdu ext desc for the packet.
This will eventually make the packet drop in firmware and
lead to traffic stall. As the fast Tx path ath12k_wifi7_dp_tx_fast()
is being chose using skb->fast_xmit along skb->mark field for link_id
info. So add the skb->mark check also in skb->flags filling condition.

Fixes:  I86fd570944dc ("QSDK:DP:wifi:ath12k:Add KPI improvemnts for TCP DL")
Patch dependency: 0516-0002-QSDK-DP-wifi-ath12k-Optimizations-for-KPI-performanc.patch

Signed-off-by: Tamizh Chelvam Raja <tamizhr@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c
index 0c81cc6..4f66151 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c
@@ -1345,7 +1345,9 @@ static void ath12k_wifi7_mac_op_tx(struct ieee80211_hw *hw,
 	}
 
 	link_id = u32_get_bits(info->control.flags, IEEE80211_TX_CTRL_MLO_LINK);
-	if (unlikely(!skb->fast_xmit || !hw->perf_mode)) {
+	if (unlikely(!(skb->fast_xmit &&
+		     ((skb->mark & ATH12K_MLO_METADATA_MLO_ASSIST_TAG_MASK) ==
+		      ATH12K_MLO_METADATA_MLO_ASSIST_TAG)) || !hw->perf_mode)) {
 		memset(skb_cb, 0, sizeof(*skb_cb));
 		skb_cb->vif = vif;
 
-- 
